Tutorial 3 - Predefined Shapes - Ellipses / Circles
Shows the basics of Ellipses / Circles to create Arcs and Segments. Two example drawings - Who nibbled the pie and Radiation warning sign.

Ellipse Tool (F5)
 -Integer Ratio (Hold Ctrl)
 -Centre start point (Hold Shift)

Edit Paths (F2)
 -Create Arc (Drag Inside)
 -Create Segment (Drag Ouside)

Select & Transform Objects (F1)
 -Resize (Click Once)
 -Rotate / Skew (Click Twice)

Example 1 - Who Nibbled the Pie?
 -Duplicate (Ctrl D)

Example 2 - Radiation Symbol